doc.after: Human activities have threatened many migratory bird species The distances involved in bird migration mean that they often cross political boundaries of countries and conservation measures require international cooperation Several international treaties have been signed to protect migratory species including the Migratory Bird Treaty Act of 1918 of the US 95 and the African Eurasian Migratory Waterbird Agreement 96
